name: ZXing 3.5.1
body:
- Various minor bug fixes, including more from oss-fuzz
- Avoid very long detection of QR codes in two types of pathological cases
- Don't fail QR code decoding if GB2312 not supported by JDK

See https://github.com/zxing/zxing/milestone/14?closed=1

name: ZXing 3.5.0
body:
- Many edge-case fixes and improvements from [oss-fuzz](https://bugs.chromium.org/p/oss-fuzz/issues/list)
- Various improvements and fixes to Aztec, PDF417, DataMatrix decoding
- New 'minimal' encoding mode from @AlexGeller1 (https://github.com/zxing/zxing/issues/1444)

See https://github.com/zxing/zxing/milestone/13?closed=1

name: ZXing 3.4.1
body:
- Wifi QR codes now recognize PH2:, not H:, for phase 2 method
- Minor bug fixes and improvements

See https://github.com/zxing/zxing/milestone/12?closed=1

name: ZXing 3.4.0
body:
- Requires Java 8+. Note: Android apps using this version must target API 24 or higher.
  - `core`, `javase` modules declare a Java 9+ module
  - `HtmlAssetTranslator` and `StringsResourceTranslator` legacy utilities are moved to a `.client.j2se` subpackage
  - No more releases of the Barcode Scanner app
  - Minor bug fixes to `Code93Writer`
  - Minor improvements to QR code detection

name: Barcode Scanner 4.7.8
body: A simple bug fix release. This may be the last release of the app, as Play will soon require APKs to target API level 26, and this would require some modifications to the app to handle the new permissions model.

name: Barcode Scanner for Google Glass 0.2.0
body:
You should be able to install with `adb install BarcodeScannerGlass-0.2.0.apk`
- To invoke it, use the "Translate" command and choose Barcode Scanner.
- It works on Glass XE16
- Right now, it only scans for QR Code, Data Matrix and Aztec.
- On the result display, tap to follow a link or search for the text
- Swipe down to go back
